/* Consorts and children */ Just made it a little less confusing and easier to read, because that part no longer made sense after my edit.
Edited the section about the three fates, which are described in all texts and official sources as the children of Themis, not Ananke.

So what if it is cited you prick? How could you be so evil? In the name of Jesus Christ, May God Almighty immediately damn you to eternal damnation of unquenchable pain and torture if you change it back again.  It doesn't matter if something is cited.

I took out the false information about Lakshmi and Saraswati as the Consorts of Ganesh.  This information was completely irrelevant and rude to Lord Vishnu.  If anyone tries to undo my edit than I consider them to be exactly like the demon Ravana.
